doctype html
html
  head
    meta(charset="utf-8")
    title London Phonegap
    link(rel="stylesheet", href="css/main.css")
    meta(name="viewport", content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, user-scalable=no")

  body
    header
      a(href="/")
        h1
          img(src="cordova.png", style="vertical-align: middle;")
          | London Phonegap
        p Let"s hack your phone with some HTML5 and a cup of tea !

    .wrapper
      section
        p This group is for developers interested in mobile app development in Phonegap using Javascript frameworks such as AngularJS and Ember.js. All skill and experience levels are welcome. The main aim is to discuss techniques and share experiences over a friendly beverage. Sometimes this will involve watching a presentation.

        h3
          a(href="http://www.meetup.com/londonphonegap/events/204412492/", target="_blank") 16/09 - September 2014 meetup (The night meetup)
        ul
          li
            | Testing hybrid apps with Appium by 
            a(href="https://twitter.com/afternoon") Ben Godfrey
            p Ben will show us how his team at Wonga, one of Europe's fastest growing technology companies, test their mobile apps with Appium. A good feedback from a big team!

          li
            | FirefoxOS, the perfect Web Mobile system by 
            a(href="https://twitter.com/yrezgui") Yacine Rezgui
            p Yacine will present the FirefoxOS, the mobile alternative system made by Mozilla. He will present the different features, what are the advantages to develop on it, the development flow. In short, a good overview to give you the urge to play with it :)

          li
            | Phonegap Frameworks (How far We Have Come) by 
            a(href="https://twitter.com/saniyusuf") Sani Yusuf
            p Sanif will show an overview of all the different mobile frameworks that works with Phonegap: Ionic Framework, Famo.us, Ratchet, etc.

        hr

        h2 Past events

        h3
          a(href="http://www.meetup.com/londonphonegap/events/187350322/", target="_blank") 16/06 - June 2014 meetup (The night meetup)
        ul
          li
            | Verifying a PhoneGap build with Smoke Tests & Appium by 
            a(href="https://twitter.com/ezodude") Ezo Saleh
            p Ezo showed us how to test PhoneGap apps with smoke tests and Appium. Appium is an open source test automation framework for use with native and hybrid mobile apps. It drives iOS and Android apps using the WebDriver JSON wire protocol. No more excuse for testing your apps! 

          li
            | Why JavaScript devs should learn Swift? by 
            a(href="https://twitter.com/jamiltz") James Nocentini
            p James presented Swift, the new Apple language for iOS & Mac OS and how building Phonegap plugins will be easier with it.

        h3
          a(href="http://www.meetup.com/londonphonegap/events/174986552/", target="_blank") 22/04 - April 2014 meetup (The night meetup)
        ul
          li
            | Build Nobackend apps with PouchDB by 
            a(href="https://twitter.com/jamiltz") James Nocentini
            p James showed us how to make a real offline mobile app and how PouchDB help him to avoid creating a backend.

          li
            | Rendering performance with Chrome DevTools by 
            a(href="https://twitter.com/gauntface") Matt Gaunt
            p Matt showed us how to optimize and debug your mobile application with the DevTools. So cool !

        h3
          a(href="http://www.meetup.com/londonphonegap/events/168417212/", target="_blank") 13/03 - March Morning Meetup

        h3
          a(href="http://www.meetup.com/londonphonegap/events/158018072/", target="_blank") 03/02 - February 2014 meetup (The night meetup)
        ul
          li
            | Ionic, Electric app development by 
            a(href="https://twitter.com/yrezgui") Yacine Rezgui
            p This talk will introduce the Ionic Framework and will explore the different models of mobile apps (html5, native, hybrid).

          li
            | One for all? by 
            a(href="https://twitter.com/sheppyc") Chris Shepherd
            p Chris takes us through his experiences of building multi-platform apps from a single source.

        h3
          a(href="http://www.meetup.com/londonphonegap/events/155050162/", target="_blank") 19/12 - Inaugural morning meetup

